title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Create a Wayang plan that finds all the purchases in the household appliances file for purchases made in october 2025. It should only include purchases for organisation which have more than 10 departments, also return the creditor name of these purchases as well as the price and the purchase line. Output in a textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log: Create a Wayang plan that retrieves all purchases from the Household Appliances file with purchase dates in October 2025. Filter to include only entries where the purchasing organization has more than 10 departments. For each resulting purchase, return the creditor name, the price, and the purchase line. Output the results to a text file.

log.thoughts: To satisfy the query: need purchases from factpurchases filtered by date (invoice_date in Oct 2025) and by description matching household_appliances text file; join with creditor to get creditor name; ensure organisation has >10 departments by using department counts; thus include factpurchases, creditor, department and the household_appliances text file.

steps.detailed_description: Load factpurchases, creditor, department tables and household_appliances text file as inputs. Include all relevant columns for later joins: factpurchases (purchase_id, organisation_id, department_id, creditor_id, invoice_id, invoice_date, invoice_line_no, invoice_line_descr, invoice_line_price), creditor (creditor_id, name), department (department_id, organisation_id), household_appliances (text lines listing appliance items).

Join factpurchases with creditor to retrieve creditor name, and filter by: invoice_date in October 2025, and that the organisation has more than 10 departments (i.e., for the organisation_id referenced in factpurchases, count of department rows with that organisation_id > 10). Also filter purchases where invoice_line_descr matches any line from the household_appliances text file. Output should include: creditor name, invoice_line_price, and invoice_line_descr (purchase line) for each resulting row.
Write the resulting dataset to a text file (e.g., purchases_oct2025_filtered.txt) containing the creditor name, price, and purchase line for each qualifying purchase.

log.thoughts: Three steps: load all inputs, perform a binary join/filtering to enforce date, organisation size, and item-match constraints, then output the final selected fields to a text file.

This sets up data for later filtering based on invoice_date in October 2025, organisation department counts, and appliance-based filtering in subsequent steps.

log.thoughts: Refined plan to: (a) filter purchases by October 2025, (b) compute organisations with more than 10 departments, (c) retain only purchases from such organisations when linked to Household Appliances entries, and (d) join with creditor to surface creditor name and price; finally project creditor name, price and purchase line and write to text output.
